links.title: Twitter users encounter interface changes as election nears
links.description: Twitter has rolled out changes it's made to the interface to slow down information amplification as the U.S. election enters its home stretch. It had previously announced how it would be applying its Civic Integrity Policy on and around election night, including labeling tweets that falsely claim a win for any candidate, and removing tweets encouraging violence or interference with results or polling places.
